\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b viscosa}: Leaves 1- to 3-foliolate. Primary branches of inflorescence longer than leaves; arista 6-15 mm. Corolla exceeding the calyx, yellow. Legume exceeding calyx. Seeds numerous. {\i  C. & W. Mediterranean region; S. & N.E. Portugal. }
\par

\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b brachycarpa} (DC.) Batt. in Batt. & Trabut,{\i   Fl. Algér.} ({\i  Dicot.}) 212 (1889): Leaves 1- to 5-foliolate. Primary branches of the inflorescence 14-18 mm; arista 2-6 mm. Corolla 9-11 mm, slightly exceeding the calyx, yellow, rarely with pink veins. Legume c. 8 mm, about equalling the calyx.{\i   Spain and Portugal}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b breviflora} (DC.) Nyman,{\i   Consp. }161 (1878) ({\i  O. breviflora} DC.): Middle cauline leaves 3-foliolate, rarely all leaves 1-foliolate; apex of leaflets often emarginate. Primary branches of the inflorescence equalling or shorter than leaves; arista 6-15 mm. Corolla shorter than calyx. Legume 12-18 mm. Seeds numerous.{\i   Almost throughout the range of the species.}
\par

\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b d}) Subsp. {\b sieberi} (Besser ex DC.) Sirj., {\i  Beih. Bot. Centr.}{\b  49 }({\b 2}): 526 (1932) ({\i  O. sieberi }Besser ex DC.): Leaves 1- to 3-foliolate. Primary branches of the inflorescence shorter than leaves, often nearly muticous; flowers aggregated at apices of branches. Corolla exceeding calyx, standard often pink. Legume rather longer than calyx. Seeds 4-6. •{\i   From Sardegna to Kriti. }

\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b e}) Subsp. {\b subcordata} (Cav.) Sirj.,{\i   op. cit.} 527 (1932): Stems 15-25 cm, glabrous below. Leaves all 1-foliolate; leaflets subcordate. Primary branches of the inflorescence up to twice as long as leaves; arista 6-15 mm. Corolla yellow. Legume 2-3 times as long as calyx.{\i   S. Spain}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b f}) Subsp. {\b foetida} (Schousboe ex DC.) Sirj., {\i  op. cit.} 527 (1932): Stems up to 70 cm, rather slender, glabrous below, variably hairy above. Middle leaves 3-foliolate, leaflets acute. Primary branches of the inflorescence 3-4 times as long as leaves. Corolla pinkish-purple, exceeding calyx. Legume about equalling calyx. Seeds 3-4.{\i   S. Spain.}
\par

