\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 26. O. pusilla} L., {\i  Syst. Nat.} ed. 10,{\b  2}: 1159 (1759) ({\i  O. columnae} All.). Perennial up to 25 cm, somewhat woody at the base; stems variably hairy. Leaves 3-foliolate, long-petiolate; leaflets 5-13 mm, elliptical to suborbicular, sometimes emarginate. Flowers sessile in lax spikes, with leaf-like bracts (longer than the flowers) to the apex. Corolla 5-12 mm, yellow, about equalling the calyx. Legume 6-8 mm. Seeds c. 6, c. 2 mm, yellow-brown, minutely tuberculate.{\i   S. Europe, extending northwards to N. France and Czechoslovakia.} Al Au Bu Co Cz Ga Gr He Hs Hu It Ju Lu Rm Rs (K) Sa Si Tu [Be].
